tsconfig.js
   -file is always placed at the root

{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "es2017", // use EcmaSript standards (ES6)
    "module": "commonjs", //syntax to import and export
    "strictNullChecks": true // variables can only be null or undefined if explicitly assigned
  },
  "include": ["**/*.ts"] // compiler looks for all .ts files 
}

having one allows you to run $ tsc 

$ tsc             // transcompile all files 
$ tsc fileName.ts // transcompile specific file